Basic Food Delivery Website with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

Overview

We will create a basic food delivery website with three pages: Home, Menu, and Contact. Each page will be created using HTML for structure, CSS for styling, and JavaScript for interactivity.

Structure

index.html: Homepage

menu.html: Menu page

contact.html: Contact page

styles.css: CSS for styling

scripts.js: JavaScript file for interactivity

Step-by-Step Implementation

index.html

The homepage will include a welcome message and navigation links to the Menu and Contact pages.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Food Delivery - Home rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    


        

Welcome to Food Delivery
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="index.html">Home>
                <li><a href="menu.html">Menucontact.html">Contact
            </ul>
        </nav>>
        <section>
            

Delicious Food Delivered to Your Doorstep</h2>
            <p>Order your favorite meals with our convenient and fast food delivery service.


        </section>
    </main>
    <script src="scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

menu.html

The menu page will display a list of food items with descriptions and prices.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Food Delivery - Menu rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    


        

Our Menu</h1>
        <nav
                

Homemenu.html">Menu
                <li><a href="contact.html">Contact>
            </ul>
        </nav>>
        <section>
            

Available Dishes</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Pizza - $10
                <li>Burger - $8</li>
                

Pasta - $12</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
    <script src="scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

contact.html

The contact page will include a form for users to get in touch.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Food Delivery - Contact
</head>
<body>
    


        

Contact Us
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="index.html">Home>menu.html">Menu>
                <li>Contact>
            </ul>
        </nav>>
        <section>
            

Get in Touch
            <form id="contactForm">
                <label for="name">Name:
                <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
                
                <label for="email">Email:
                <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
                
                <label for="message">Message:
                <textarea id="message" name="message" required></textarea>

                <button type="submit">Submit</button>
            </form>
        </section>
    </main>
    <script src="scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

styles.css

We will add some basic styling for the layout and elements.

body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

header {
    background-color: #ff6347;
    color: white;
    padding: 1em 0;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
}

nav ul li {
    display: inline;
    margin: 0 1em;
}

h1, h2 {
    margin: 0.5em 0;
}

main {
    padding: 2em;
}

form label {
    display: block;
    margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em;
}

form input, form textarea {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 0.5em;
    margin-bottom: 1em;
}

form button {
    padding: 0.5em 1em;
    background-color: #ff6347;
    color: white;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

form button:hover {
    background-color: #e55347;
}

scripts.js

We will handle form submission using JavaScript.

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const contactForm = document.getElementById('contactForm');
    
    if(contactForm) {
        contactForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {
            event.preventDefault();
            alert('Form submitted successfully!');
        });
    }
});

This basic structure will give you a functional, minimalistic food delivery website with three essential pages. You can further enhance this website with more advanced features and interactivity as needed.
